## Listing Sites

> Example Request

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```
```php
<?php
$wiw = new Wheniwork("<%=@wiw_token%>");
$result = $wiw->get("sites");
?>
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "sites": [
    <%= print_json(data.objects['site'], :minimal=>true).indent(4) %>,
    <%= print_json(data.objects['site'], :minimal=>true, :include=>{'id'=>4,'name'=>'Lone Pine'}).indent(4) %>
  ]
}
```

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites`



## Get Existing Site

> Example Request

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/9 \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```
```php
<?php
$wiw = new Wheniwork("<%=@wiw_token%>");
$result = $wiw->get("sites/9");
?>
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "site": <%= print_json(data.objects['site'], :minimal=>true).indent(2) %>
}
```

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/{id}`

### Parameters

Key | Description
--- | -----------
id | ID of the site requested.


## Create/Update Site

### Create HTTP Request
`POST <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/`

### Update HTTP Requests
`PUT <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/{id}`

### Parameters

The `POST` and/or `PUT` body can include fields from the [Site Object](#sites).


## Delete Existing Site

> Example Request

```shell
curl -X DELETE <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/9 \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```
```php
<?php
$wiw = new Wheniwork("<%=@wiw_token%>");
$result = $wiw->delete("sites/9");
?>
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "success": true
}
```

### HTTP Request
`DELETE <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/{site_id}`

### Parameters

Key | Description
